label.value: decreased succinate dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of succinate dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity is decreased.

label.value: increased succinate dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of succinate dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity is increased.

label.value: normal sulfite reductase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of sulfite reductase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal reactive oxygen species level during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of reactive oxygen species (ROS) measured in a cell that is subject to nitrogen starvation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased RNA level during cellular response to diethyl maleate

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to diethyl maleate is lower than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: resistance to copper

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of copper ions than normal.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K9 dimethylation at telomere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in telomeric regions does not occur.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 dimethylation at subtelomeric heterochromatin during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in heterochromatin at subtelomeric regions occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 dimethylation at telomere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in telomeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: altered level of substance in cell during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of a specific substance measured in a cell that is subject to nitrogen starvation differs from normal.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: increased cellular glutathione level during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of glutathione (GSH) measured in a cell that is subject to nitrogen starvation is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular glutathione level during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of glutathione (GSH) measured in a cell that is subject to nitrogen starvation is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased RNA polymerase II proximal promoter sequence-specific DNA binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which DNA binding at an RNA polymerase II proximal promoter by a gene product is decreased, when a gene or the bound DNA sequence is mutated. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene. An RNA polymerase II proximal promoter is a sequence of DNA that is in cis with and relatively close to a core promoter for RNA polymerase II.

label.value: increased cellular nitrite level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of nitrite (NO2-) ions measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased catalase activity during cellular response to nitrosative stress

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of catalase activity is decreased during a cellular response to nitrosative stress.

label.value: abnormal pyridoxine:NADP 4-dehydrogenase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of pyridoxine:NADP 4-dehydrogenase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased pyridoxine:NADP 4-dehydrogenase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of pyridoxine:NADP 4-dehydrogenase activity is decreased.

label.value: increased pyridoxine:NADP 4-dehydrogenase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of pyridoxine:NADP 4-dehydrogenase activity is increased.

label.value: normal pyridoxamine-phosphate oxidase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of pyridoxamine-phosphate oxidase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal pyridoxal kinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of pyridoxal kinase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased cellular pyridoxamine 5'-phosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of pyridoxamine 5'-phosphate measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cellular pyridoxine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of pyridoxine measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased cellular pyridoxal level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of pyridoxal measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased flocculation in stationary phase

value.value: A cell population phenotype that reflects increased occurrence of flocculation when the population is in stationary phase. Flocculation is the non-sexual aggregation of single cells.

label.value: normal protein phosphorylation during cellular response to heat

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to heat.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein level during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during mitosis is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein level during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during mitosis is higher than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: elongated vegetative cell with fragmented septum and more than four nuclei

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which vegetative a cell is elongated, and contains more than four nuclei and pieces of a septum that does not completely bisect the cell.

label.value: abnormal homologous chromosome segregation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which homologous chromosome segregation is abnormal. Homologous chromosome segregation is the process in which replicated homologous chromosomes are organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two sets during the first division of the meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: normal meiotic spindle

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the meiotic spindle is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) with respect to structure, composition, location, and orientation.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at RNA polymerase II-transcribed genes during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to regions of chromatin containing genes that can be transcribed by RNA polymerase II is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: loss of viability upon glucose starvation

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a smaller than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable when cells the population are subject to glucose starvation.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate experiments in which a culture is grown under glucose-depleted conditions, and then the number of cells viable enough to form a colony upon return to conditions supporting vegetative growth is measured and compared to wild type. Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: increased viability upon glucose starvation

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a larger than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable when cells the population are subject to glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: increased cellular reactive oxygen species level in stationary phase

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of reactive oxygen species (ROS) measured in a cell is higher than normal when the population in which the cell is found is in stationary phase.

label.value: normal glucose consumption

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of glucose consumed by cells in a given time is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased oxygen consumption during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of oxygen consumed by cells in a given time is higher than in wild type.

label.value: increased cell population growth on glycerol carbon source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cell growth is increased relative to normal in a medium containing glycerol as the carbon source.

definition.value: Note that trace amounts of another carbon source are usually required for S. pombe growth on glycerol; yeast extract-based rich medium supplies the trace substance, but minimal medium must be supplemented. It is therefore important to annotate the growth medium as an experimental condition when using this term. Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: normal viability in stationary phase during glucose starvation

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable after entering stationary phase, under conditions of glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: decreased RNA level in stationary phase

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell is lower than normal when the population in which the cell is found is in stationary phase. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K9 dimethylation at centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in centromeric regions does not occur.

label.value: normal RNA level during glucose starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell that is subject to glucose starvation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term. Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: decreased protein kinase activity during cellular response to heat

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a protein kinase activity is decreased during a cellular response to heat.

label.value: decreased protein phosphorylation during cellular response to heat

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a lower extent than normal during a cellular response to heat.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: h+ specific sterility

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which conjugation does not occur in cells of the h+ mating type.

label.value: decreased mating efficiency in h- cells

value.value: A biological process phenotype in which the observed mating efficiency, as determined by counting zygotes, asci, and sometimes spores, is lower than normal in cells of the h- mating type.

definition.value: Note that mating efficiency is often measured by counting zygotes plus asci, sometimes also including spores, so a change in measured mating efficiency may reflect a change in conjugation frequency (see FYPO:0000031 and its descendants), a change in sporulation (see FYPO:0000121 and its descendants), or both. For this reason, this term is not a child of 'mating phenotype' (FYPO:0000031).

label.value: decreased RNA level during cellular response to pheromone and nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to a pheromone that occurs when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation is lower than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased RNA level during nitrogen starvation in h- cells

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell of the h- mating type when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased RNA level during nitrogen starvation in h+ cells

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell of the h+ mating type when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein aggregate fusion

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which small aggregates of misfolded protein fuse into larger aggregates to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: increased cellular protein aggregate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein present as aggregates of misfolded protein is greater than normal.
